    <text id="F6073T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p><unclear>Garbish</unclear> thanks Brewer for his kind letter at Christmas,
                    mentions a claim handled by Brewer, and discusses the illness of relatives.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
            

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-12-28">Dec 28. 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Pittsburgh</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Brewer</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your letter with its illuminated accompaniment was handed me this morning by
                    Charley and was welcomed as a <unclear>genuine</unclear> Christmas gift. I am
                    very much obliged for the trouble you have had in in securing for me, the long
                    coming claim.</p>

                <p>I am glad to learn you are all well + flourishing. Long may you
                    <unclear>wave</unclear>. My wife and <unclear>May</unclear> here both been quite
                    unwell a considerable portion of the winter but are both better soon + able to
                    be almost as usual.</p>

                <p>Remember me to my old company in arms + greet them with a happy new year. We are
                    very <unclear>long</unclear> just now as this<pb n="2"/>time is our harvest.</p>

                <p>Accept my thanks for your kindess, kind regards to your family + believe me.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours as <unclear>ever</unclear></salute>
                    <signed>John <unclear>Garbish</unclear></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Excuse <unclear>handwriting</unclear></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
